Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.41,0:00:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Na shimmering nebula!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.16,0:00:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan's logic is good medicine\Nfor hearts dried by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.69,0:00:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is in a general\Nhospital! Old Mori's a killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.30,0:00:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.78,0:00:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.63,0:00:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.17,0:01:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The General Hospital Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:01:59.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,East Beika General Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.94,0:02:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.98,0:02:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the old man's\N3rd week in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.44,0:02:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He broke his leg while\Ntrying to catch a criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.24,0:02:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but naturally, I took him down instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.91,0:02:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you've been so busy lately\Nthat this is a good chance to relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.96,0:02:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's meal time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.92,0:02:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Food, at last!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.46,0:02:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The famous detective\Nsure has an appetite!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.26,0:02:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How I'd love some beer and {\i1}sashimi{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not how a famous\Ndetective acts, Dad! How pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:52.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakayama Kazumi (26) Nurse
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.81,0:02:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But everyone is gossiping about\Nwanting to see the famous Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:02:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nurses in white, gossiping about me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.36,0:02:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.44,0:03:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to hear some stories, myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:04.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shirai Mitsuo (40) Physician
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.86,0:03:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could learn a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.12,0:03:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're too kind, Dr. Shirai...\NHow embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Learn a lot of what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.37,0:03:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful you're not made\Ninto a guinea pig, Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.29,0:03:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:19.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Eto Katsutoshi (40) Surgeon
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooooh! What a scary look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.55,0:03:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective, if I'm ever killed,\NDr. Shirai will have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.27,0:03:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Eto-{\i1}kun{\i0}, a fellow surgeon.\NWe attended college together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a sharp tongue,\Nbut he's a talented surgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.03,0:03:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may be talented, but he's a jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.54,0:03:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's started raining. Maybe we\Nshould get going, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.54,0:03:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}, you can't have alcohol,\Nbut you can have some coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I trouble you for a story?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.38,0:04:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.43,0:04:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This latest case was a good one\NI solved using my great skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was ripe with mystery, as the\Nkiller had left not a thing behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.31,0:04:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes! He's got a real sweet tooth!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Dr. Shirai?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.79,0:04:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.22,0:04:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's being murdered!\NCall 110! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.55,0:04:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.90,0:05:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This room is empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I could swear it was in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The body disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only possibility,\Nbut I did see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure there ever was one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you doubting me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a fact that\Nthere was nothing--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. It's late.\NYou'll disturb the patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.60,0:05:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it a night--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor! I saw it with my own two eyes--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.98,0:05:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been quite exhausted lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.27,0:05:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I did fall asleep\Nwhile telling you my story...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.99,0:05:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the famous detective was tired.\NTalk about a panic monger...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we'll be leaving, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the old man witnessed the\Nsame thing many more times!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.23,0:06:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.36,0:06:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,110! Call 110!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.98,0:06:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.99,0:06:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you, Dad?!\NThis is the fourth time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying! I really did see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.17,0:06:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.88,0:06:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only guess that the stress of\Ndealing with all those crimes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has gotten to him and\Ncaused him to hallucinate...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Those were no hallucinations!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.98,0:07:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Calm down!\NPull yourself together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happened to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll check it out just to be safe...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These blotches were recently made...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It did rain twice during the\Ntime he witnessed the murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,\Nthis window was open then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His room is diagonal from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.90,0:07:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No curtains... Is that an unused room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.74,0:07:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the lights are on\Nin that room at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:08:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the dark building behind it will\Ncause the window to act like a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.37,0:08:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, depending on the\Nangle of the open window,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.00,0:08:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it'll project into a certain room...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.59,0:08:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the old man's!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real room isn't\Nvisible from his window.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.09,0:08:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's in that room...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.72,0:08:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is reflected onto this window...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.01,0:08:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and looks to him as\Nif it's happening in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a mirror trick involving windows!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:28.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Storeroom
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.52,0:08:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A first-aid dummy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They used this to act it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.30,0:08:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this just a prank, or is there\Nanother reason behind it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna stay with\Nhim tonight to look after him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.06,0:09:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How nice of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.15,0:09:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0},\Ntake these and get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really coming down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.56,0:09:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.52,0:09:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan! Did you see that, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.94,0:09:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That was no hallucination!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.57,0:09:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think so!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.07,0:09:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ok!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Kogoro's back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:07.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Storeroom
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nobody here,\Nand the dummy hasn't been used...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.01,0:10:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.55,0:10:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.23,0:10:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.23,0:10:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Eto!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two stab wounds on the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.15,0:10:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there were no vital\Nreactions on the second one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.24,0:10:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the first killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.20,0:10:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not entirely sure, myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone suddenly hit me and...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.59,0:10:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:10:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.30,0:11:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.97,0:11:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.14,0:11:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, either-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.22,0:11:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san {\i0}killed Eto-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.06,0:11:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't surprise me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me, but who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}'s doctor, Shirai.\NI'm on night duty tonight...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that this doesn't surprise you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mori-{\i1}san {\i0}has been under a\Nlot of stress lately, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.20,0:11:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he even had recurring hallucinations,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I was worried he might\Ndo something like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.88,0:11:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.92,0:11:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I saw the murder\Nin the opposite room, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how you feel, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.93,0:11:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but your testimony would be\Ndeemed as a cover for Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.55,0:11:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and most likely won't hold up in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.81,0:11:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.93,0:11:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...come to think of it, my memory\Ndoes go blank sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could have easily committed\Na murder during then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.03,0:12:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.36,0:12:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop being stupid!\NPull yourself together, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.49,0:12:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, Ran-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.99,0:12:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, from the locations\Nof the room, stairs, elevators,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.25,0:12:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and nurse stations, it's unlikely\Nthe killer snuck in from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.13,0:12:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, I hear you and the\Nvictim had heated disagreements?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.59,0:12:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing that big!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, could I have your alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.43,0:12:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It happened at 11:30, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.44,0:12:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in my own room on\Nthe 2nd floor of the north ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.28,0:12:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you prove this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.74,0:12:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okita-{\i1}kun{\i0}. You delivered my\Ncharts at about that time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.03,0:12:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was around then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.37,0:12:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're certain he\Nwas in the room at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.54,0:12:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He was on the phone, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.50,0:13:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.76,0:13:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Shirai.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought your charts.\NAnd some coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.89,0:13:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.22,0:13:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on the phone, so could\Nyou just leave 'em on the desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.35,0:13:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.40,0:13:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just then that all this happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.52,0:13:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, although you didn't see him,\Nyou're sure you spoke with him
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and not a recording?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.74,0:13:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.49,0:13:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So my alibi checks out, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what kind of call was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.33,0:13:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you call them, or did they call you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.91,0:13:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.58,0:13:44.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An anonymous person had called\Nto complain about my diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.42,0:13:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You get them once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.59,0:13:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, we can't ID the caller.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Mori-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}is the most suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.10,0:13:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.27,0:14:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Shirai's alibi\Ndoes seem airtight. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.98,0:14:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Shirai clearly opened\Nthe old man's curtains
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and set the alarm clock
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.70,0:14:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he would witness\Nthose murder scenes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.96,0:14:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that alibi of his...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.83,0:14:20.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shirai
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.88,0:14:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A speakerphone...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.48,0:14:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't use any sugar...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Now I understand his alibi trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.24,0:14:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it!\NThe killer was Dr. Shirai!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have no proof...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.79,0:15:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Could this coffee cup...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister Examiner!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.34,0:15:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the boy staying with Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.76,0:15:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things don't look so good this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.76,0:15:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, Inspector Megure said\Nhe wants you to check something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.02,0:15:20.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shirai
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.02,0:15:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it was just like you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.65,0:15:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.44,0:15:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found proof on the coffee cup\Nthat Dr. Shirai was the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.17,0:15:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.75,0:15:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.34,0:15:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on, Megure-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.09,0:15:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! This is the unique\Npose "Sleeping Kogoro" takes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.68,0:15:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when using his logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.68,0:16:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a cleverly devised\Ntwo-step crime, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.69,0:16:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first step was to mentally\Ndrive me into a corner enough
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to convince me and everyone\Nelse that I committed a murder
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.15,0:16:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,out of stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second step was\Nto commit that murder
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.70,0:16:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then execute his alibi trick\Nto avoid being suspected himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.41,0:16:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To do so, he first used the first-aid\Ndummy in the fourth floor storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.50,0:16:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer opened the murder\Nroom window at a certain angle
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.97,0:16:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and made his fake murders\Nin the storeroom reflect off of it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that I would see it from the south ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.06,0:16:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, at 11:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he called the victim into\Nthe room and murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like his previous acts,\Nbut this time for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Conan and I witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.28,0:17:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how could he get you\Nto witness it so conveniently?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.25,0:17:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To do that, the killer visited\Nmy room, opened the curtains,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.21,0:17:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had me take an adjusted\Namount of sleeping medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, he set the alarm clock\Nto 11:30, the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.64,0:17:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then knocked me out with a\Nblunt object after I rushed into the room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.27,0:17:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and put the knife in my\Nhand to get my fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.23,0:17:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who, exactly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.44,0:17:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.78,0:17:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what you want to say, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Dr. Eto's murderer was you, Dr. Shirai!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.50,0:17:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have an alibi, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.96,0:17:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.79,0:17:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had her deliver the charts then,\Nand he even talked with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a recording, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.30,0:18:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.01,0:18:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.89,0:18:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, the doctor called his cell\Nphone from his room just after 11:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turned on the speaker, and went\Nto the murder room in the north ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then murdered Dr. Eto,\Nwho he had called there ahead of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,used the body to act\Nout a murder at 11:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.54,0:18:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then used his cell phone to converse\Nwith the nurse over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.96,0:18:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when I arrived on the scene,\Nhe hit me with a blunt object,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.22,0:18:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,knocked me out, and put the knife\Nin my hands to put my prints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.01,0:18:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, he returned to his\Nroom during the commotion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.39,0:18:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and turned the phone off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.85,0:18:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must have felt quite\Nrelieved that it was all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.53,0:18:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he made one big oversight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.86,0:19:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The coffee the\Nnurse kindly brought him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.61,0:19:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume you all know\NDr. Shirai has a real sweet tooth?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.99,0:19:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the coffee's\Nsugar hadn't been used at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.21,0:19:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means Dr. Shirai\Nhadn't drunk the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.38,0:19:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous. Even I take\Nit without sugar sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.01,0:19:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would hardly call that proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, then you did drink it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but if you're going to say\Nhow there was no saliva on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.64,0:19:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that might be because\NI gave it a quick rinse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.94,0:19:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something else missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.28,0:19:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.57,0:19:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your fingerprints.\NThere aren't any on the coffee cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I rinsed it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.49,0:19:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the fingerprints of the nurse\Nwho brought it are on the handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.25,0:20:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying you washed off\Nyour fingerprints from on top of hers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.88,0:20:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.30,0:20:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, when you rinsed the\Ncoffee cup, you had gloves on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.93,0:20:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The surgical gloves you\Nhad used during the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was he wearing gloves before then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.81,0:20:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he returned to\Nhis room after the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he probably still had\Nthe weapon he hit me with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't get his prints\Non it before he disposed of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.28,0:20:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, once back in his room,\Nhe felt he had to down the coffee,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.37,0:20:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or else his alibi of being in\Nthe room would seem suspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.12,0:20:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he hurriedly poured it out,\Nwith gloves still on, and rinsed the cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.22,0:20:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But only the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.18,0:20:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that reason, only the nurse's\Nfingerprints remained on the cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.14,0:20:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you drank the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.19,0:20:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any other reasons your\Nfingerprints weren't on the handle?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.90,0:21:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving evidence because of the\Ngloves I wore to leave no evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you admit to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.99,0:21:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all as Mori-{\i1}san{\i0} said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.54,0:21:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? What was your motive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our chief surgeon is being\Nforced to retire next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eto and I were the\Ncandidates for his position...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.42,0:21:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Eto blackmailed me into declining!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.05,0:21:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice but\Nto accept his demand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.43,0:21:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He knew I had bought\Nmy way into medical school.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.69,0:21:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the professor\NI paid off was his father!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.03,0:21:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I ever pay out all\Nthat money to get into school?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, crime and\Ndishonesty doesn't pay, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.81,0:23:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate this! I'm through\Nwith this Sleeping Kogoro stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.94,0:23:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How come? You solved\Nthat case easily enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.19,0:23:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.27,0:23:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.82,0:23:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess old Sleeping Kogoro\Nis still going strong after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.93,0:23:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He never learns...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:25.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.67,0:24:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Teacher! Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.58,0:24:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After she was knocked\Nout with chloroform,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.76,0:24:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she was strangled with a rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.85,0:24:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are still tracks here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.51,0:24:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The front door...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.05,0:24:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the killer\Nis still inside this lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.23,0:24:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.79,0:24:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Ski Lodge Murder Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.38,0:24:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.84,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heater.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.84,0:24:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is a two-parter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.42,0:24:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Part one, part one, part one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.57,0:24:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
